INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('312', '1', '2013-10-23 10:45:24', '2013-10-23 10:45:24', '<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/EqbqPwNGxPU?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>When arrested for DWI you only have 15 days to request a hearing to save your drivers license</strong>\r\n\r\n<h2>Did you knowâ¦</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Driving under the influence (DUI) and driving while intoxicated (DWI) are <strong>two separate charges</strong> in Texas?</li>\r\n	<li>If you have been charged with drunk driving, you can face both criminal <strong>and</strong> civil penalties?</li>\r\n	<li>You only have <strong>15 days</strong> after you have been arrested to request a hearing if you want to save your driverâs license?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese are only a few of the details you must consider if you are charged with DWI in North Texas, and they are ones you canât afford to deal with alone. You need help from an experienced DWI attorney in Texas you can trust â one who is deeply committed to protecting your rights.\r\n\r\nFortunately, the Texas DWI attorneys at Bowen Law Group are here to help. Our law firm provides a number of criminal defense services to adults and juveniles, including private drivers with occupational driverâs licenses (ODL). We pride ourselves on being some of the most focused and accomplished attorneys in Denton, Texas.\r\n<h3>A Comprehensive DWI Defense</h3>\r\nFor people who have been charged with drunk driving, the idea of facing criminal and civil penalties can be overwhelming. Many individuals who contact our office in Denton worry about the loss of their driverâs license, or other repercussions. The lawyers at Bowen Law Group have the knowledge and experience to handle all aspects of your Denton DWI defense, including the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Administrative license hearings</li>\r\n	<li>Driverâs License Appeals</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal hearings</li>\r\n	<li>Plea agreements, trials and appeals</li>\r\n	<li>Drug charge defense</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>A Prosecutorâs Advantage</h3>\r\nAs a former prosecutor, Brent D. Bowen has worked on hundreds of DWI cases, and therefore knows how to anticipate and respond to the stateâs case effectively. Not only that, but our criminal attorneys in Denton work hard to stay well-informed about changes that occur in Texas DWI laws. Although most DWI cases are resolved by agreement, our lawyers also have the litigation experience to fight for your rights and interests if your case goes to trial. Our goal is simple: to protect your freedoms and be the best advocates we can be for you.\r\n\r\nIf youâd like to learn more about our DWI defense or other criminal defense services, contact us to schedule a free consultation with an attorney at our office in Denton. We would be happy to evaluate your case for you. We serve individuals who live throughout North Texas, including the counties of Denton, Collin, Tarrant, Wise and Cooke.\r\n\r\nYouâre not alone. You have options. Call the Bowen Law Group to find out what they are.', ' DWI Defense', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dwi-defense', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:45:24', '2013-10-23 10:45:24', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=312', '0', 'page', '', '0');
