INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('336', '1', '2013-10-23 10:53:45', '2013-10-23 10:53:45', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Denton, Texas, Attorney for Juvenile Law Issues</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe width=\"600\" height=\"338\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/ckivCodlNas?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\r\n\r\nKids and teens are not adults, and â unless the allegations are especially serious â Texas law does not treat them that way. In Texas, juvenile cases are civil rather than criminal in nature.\r\n\r\nIn order to achieve results, it is important to work with a lawyer who knows Texas juvenile law. At Bowen Law Group,Â attorneyÂ Brent Bowen is a former Denton County assistant district attorney who is experienced in defending young people in juvenile matters.\r\n\r\nOur Denton, Texas, law firm handles a wide range of offenses under Texas juvenile law:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minor in possession</li>\r\n	<li>Drug crimes</li>\r\n	<li>Assault</li>\r\n	<li>Sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Robbery</li>\r\n	<li>Shoplifting</li>\r\n	<li>Burglary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn addition to representing offenders in juvenile court, we also handle related administrative matters, like suspensions and expulsions from Texas schools. We also talk to our clients about sealing juvenile records, or expunction and non-disclosureÂ of criminal records after an offense.\r\n<h3>Quick Action for Juvenile Detention Hearings</h3>\r\nInstead of being arrested, minors are âdetainedâ or âtaken into custody.â Under Texas law, if a juvenile is detained, he or she must be held in a special facility separate from adult violators. The law requires that a detention hearing be held before a judge â usually the day after the child was taken into custody. Only a judge after a detention hearing can release a juvenile to a parent, guardian or custodian.\r\n\r\nAt Bowen Law Group, we understand the stress and worry families feel when a child has been taken into custody. We have a 24-hour, seven-day-a-week phone line so that we can respond quickly to juvenile law issues â especially when your family needs it most.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk with an attorney at Bowen Law Group, pleaseÂ contactÂ our Denton, Texas, law office at 940-566-0606. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns.', ' Juvenile Law', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'juvenile-law', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:53:45', '2013-10-23 10:53:45', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=336', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('337', '1', '2013-10-23 10:54:30', '2013-10-23 10:54:30', '<h2 id=\"areaFocus\">Sealing Your Texas Criminal Records</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe width=\"600\" height=\"338\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/i43kB2sjjwk?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\r\n\r\nSometimes a criminal record can limit your future possibilities. It can keep you from getting the right job, or from moving in to the right apartment. But a knowledgeable attorney can help you take action under Texas law, sealing these records and protecting your future.\r\n\r\nAtÂ Bowen Law Group, located in Denton, Texas, we help clients with two different methods of criminal record expungement: expunction and nondisclosure. Depending on the circumstances surrounding your detention, arrest or conviction, either one might be the right fit for you.\r\n<h3>What is the Difference Between Expunction and Non-Disclosure?</h3>\r\n<strong>Expunction:</strong>Â Expunction orders essentially erase all records of the offense â arrest records, court records and criminal history record information â from your criminal record. Expunction is only granted in certain circumstances, however. These include when a criminal case was dismissed or when you were found not guilty after a criminal trial. People who are not eligible for expunction may still be eligible for non-disclosure.\r\n\r\n<strong>Non-disclosure:</strong>Â When a petition for non-disclosure is granted, criminal justice agencies are prohibited from giving information about the offense to the public. Usually, non-disclosure is granted in certain circumstances, like when you have successfully completed a deferred adjudication. For many offenses, there is a waiting period before you can file a petition for non-disclosure. Some offenses are eligible for non-disclosure immediately.\r\n\r\nTexas law also provides for the sealing of juvenile records. If your juvenile records are ordered sealed by the court, they are removed from the criminal history database. At Bowen Law Group, we can help with this and with other issues of juvenile law.\r\n<h3>Contact Bowen Law Group</h3>\r\nTo talk about expunction or non-disclosure with a lawyerÂ at Bowen Law Group, pleaseÂ contactÂ our Denton, Texas, law office at 940-566-0606. Our phones are answered 24 hours a day, seven days a week so you can get quick responses to your legal concerns â especially when you need them most.', 'Expunction and Non-Disclosure', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'expunction-and-non-disclosure', '', '', '2013-10-23 10:54:30', '2013-10-23 10:54:30', '', '0', 'http://brentbowen.laptoppricesinpakistan.com.pk/?page_id=337', '0', 'page', '', '0');
